main event: Unidentified flying object sighted by the U.S.S. Higbee on Midway Island.
interesting points: The sighting occurred at 2330 on August 25, 1960, and lasted for approximately 10 minutes., The object appeared as a blinding white light and moved from NW to SE., It was reported to have a brightness similar to that of a first magnitude star., The object was evaluated as a possible communications balloon or satellite., The sighting was documented in a military report and a naval message.
sighted object: blinding white light in the sky
witness description: crew members of the U.S.S. Higbee
